name: Esther
comment: A tranquil oasis surrounded by barren landscape in the middle of nowhere. Tasteful set up with sheltered tables and benches, a fire pit with chairs. Drinking water. Good views and sunsets, and - depending on your fellow campers - great atmosphere. Property dogs Gypsy and Jill are awesome. Ojai is about 1.5 hour drive through Los Padres National Forest.
